place.name: STANFIELD
place.gazetteerText: STANFIELD, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; 3½ miles W by S of Elmham r. station. Post town, Litcham, under Swaffham. Acres, 903. Real property, £1,827. Pop., 195. Houses, 46. The property is sub-divided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £300.* Patron, the Rev. E. L. Davies. The church is ancient. Charities, £5. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
